"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0804-1463435-paris-2024-irish-in-action-on-day-10-of-olympic-games\", \"text\": \"The schedule eases considerably for the Irish in action on Monday at the Olympics, caveated with a big name hitting the track for the first time.  Rhasidat Adeleke will be joined by Sharlene Mawdsley and Sophie Becker in the women's 400 metres heats.  Adeleke and Mawdsley will be confident of progression, while Becker will need a superb run to reach the semi-finals.  Daniel Coyle, Cian O'Connor and Shane Sweetnam compete in the show jumping individual event.  The top 30 of 75 competitors advance to the next stage.  Finn Lynch and Eve McMahon conclude their sailing races with the top 10 advancing to the medal event.  Ciara McGing kicks off the morning's action in the 10m platform diving.  Monday 5 August  (In order of start time)  DIVING  0900-1113Women's 10m Platform -Ciara McGing  1400Women's 10m Platform semi-final if qualified  ATHLETICS  1055-1136Women's 400m:Rhasidat Adeleke, Sharlene Mawdsley, Sophie Becker  BeckerHeat 1  MawdsleyHeat 5  AdelekeHeat 6  EQUESTRIAN  1300-1700Show jumping - Individual - Daniel Coyle (Legacy), Cian O'Connor (Maurice), Shane Sweetnam (James Kann Cruz)  SAILING  1110-1206Women's dinghy race 9:Eve McMahon  1218-1314Women's dinghy race 10:Eve McMahon  1335-1431Men's dinghy race 9:Finn Lynch  1440-1536Men's dinghy race 10:Finn Lynch  \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"